    <div class="container">
        <h1><a href="https://www.abdn.ac.uk/museums/about/index.php" target="_blank" alt-text="University of Aberdeen" title="University of Aberdeen">University of Aberdeen</a></h1>
        <figure  class="right-image"><a href="https://cantaloupe.is.ed.ac.uk/iiif/2/umis-visit-aberdeen.jpg/full/full/0/default.jpg" target="_blank" alt-text="University of Aberdeen" title="University of Aberdeen"><img src="https://cantaloupe.is.ed.ac.uk/iiif/2/umis-visit-aberdeen.jpg/full/200,/0/default.jpg" /></a></figure>
        <p>The University had a museum as far back as 1727 (almost 300 years) and holds a huge range of collections that cover its full history. The collections cover archaeology and ethnography to Scottish history, coins and medals, fine art, scientific instruments, medicine, natural sciences and more.</p>
        <p>Visit the collections online at <a href="https://www.abdn.ac.uk/museums/collections/index.php" target="_blank" alt-text="Collections" title="Collections">https://www.abdn.ac.uk/museums/collections/index.php</a> or read more about the museums&rsquo; work on
            their blog: <a href="https://library.abdn.ac.uk/blog/" target="_blank" alt-text="Blog" title="Blog">https://library.abdn.ac.uk/blog/</a> You can find out more about their exhibitions and
            events at <a href="https://www.abdn.ac.uk/museums/news-events.php" target="_blank" alt-text="Events" title="Events">https://www.abdn.ac.uk/museums/news-events.php</a>.</p>
        <h3>Visiting:</h3>
        <p>For general information on visiting the museums, including accessibility information, see <a href="https://www.abdn.ac.uk/museums/about/visit-us.php" target="_blank" alt-text="Visit" title="Visit">https://www.abdn.ac.uk/museums/about/visit-us.php</a></p>
        <h3>Research visits:</h3>
        <p>To arrange a research visit, please contact <a href="mailto:museum@abdn.ac.uk">museum@abdn.ac.uk</a> or call 01224 274300.</p>
        <p>There are three museums within the University campus:</p>
        <h2><a href="https://www.abdn.ac.uk/museums/exhibitions/sdrl-679.php" target="_blank" alt-text="Sir Duncan Rice Library" title="Sir Duncan Rice Gallery">The Gallery in the Sir Duncan Rice Library</a></h2>
        <p>The Gallery has a programme of changing exhibitions throughout the year taken from the University&rsquo;s huge collection. You don&rsquo;t need to book and entry is free. For information on the latest exhibitions, visit <a href="https://www.abdn.ac.uk/museums/exhibitions/index.php" target="_blank" alt-text="Exhibitions" title="Exhibitions">https://www.abdn.ac.uk/museums/exhibitions/index.php</a></p>
        <h3>Address:</h3>
        <p>Bedford Road, Aberdeen AB24 3AA</p>
        <h3>Opening hours:</h3>
        <p>Monday &ndash; Wednesday, Friday: 10am &ndash; 5pm; Thursday: 10am &ndash; 7pm; Saturday &amp; Sunday: 11am &ndash; 4pm</p>
        <h3>Group and school visits:</h3>
        <p>For group or school visits to the Sir Duncan Rice Library Gallery, you can email Susan Curran, Curator of Learning and Outreach, on <a href="mailto:susan.curran@abdn.ac.uk">susan.curran@abdn.ac.uk</a> or call 01224 274354.</p>
        <h3>Getting there:</h3>
        <p>Parking on site is reserved for university staff, but there is pay and display parking in the surrounding roads. For directions and further information on how to get there, visit <a href="https://www.abdn.ac.uk/about/campus/maps/view/112/" target="_blank" alt-text="Directions" title="Directions">https://www.abdn.ac.uk/about/campus/maps/view/112/</a></p>
        <h3>Public transport: </h3>
        <p>The number 19 bus stops directly outside the Sir Duncan Rice Library on Bedford Road, and runs every 15 minutes.&nbsp; Bus routes 1, 2 and 20 also stop at the University campus. See First Bus timetables <a href="https://www.firstgroup.com/aberdeen/routes-and-maps/route-maps" target="_blank" alt-text="First Bus" title="First Bus">https://www.firstgroup.com/aberdeen/routes-and-maps/route-maps</a></p>
        <h3>Accessibility</h3>
        <p>For a pan-disability access guide to the Sir Duncan Rice Library, visit the <a href="https://www.accessable.co.uk/university-of-aberdeen/old-aberdeen-campus/access-guides/sir-duncan-rice-library" target="_blank" alt-text="Access Guides" title="Access Guides">AccessAble</a> website.</p>
        <h2><a href="https://www.abdn.ac.uk/museums/exhibitions/zoology-museum-588.php" target="_blank" alt-text="Zoology Museum" title="Zoology Museum">Zoology Museum</a></h2>
        <p>The museum houses the only large, international exhibition of zoological specimens in the north of Scotland. You can see insects, birds and even whales and tigers. You don&rsquo;t need to book and entry is free. For more information, visit <a href="https://www.abdn.ac.uk/museums/exhibitions/zoology-museum-588.php" target="_blank" alt-text="Visit" title="Visit">https://www.abdn.ac.uk/museums/exhibitions/zoology-museum-588.php</a></p>
        <h3>Address:</h3>
        <p>Tillydrone Ave, Aberdeen AB24 2TZ</p>
        <h3>Opening hours: </h3>
        <p>Monday &ndash; Friday: 10am &ndash; 5pm</p>
        <h3>Group and school visits:</h3>
        <p>For group and school visits to the Zoology Museum, please contact the Aberdeen Biodiversity Centre on <a href="mailto:biodiversity@abdn.ac.uk">biodiversity@abdn.ac.uk</a> or call 01224 274545 <a href="https://www.abdn.ac.uk/biodiversity/" target="_blank" alt-text="Biodiversity" title="Biodiversity">https://www.abdn.ac.uk/biodiversity/</a></p>
        <h3>Getting there:</h3>
        <p>Parking on site is reserved for university staff, but there is pay and display parking in the surrounding roads. For directions and further information on how to get there, visit <a href="https://www.abdn.ac.uk/about/campus/maps/view/113/"  target="_blank" alt-text="Maps" title="Maps">https://www.abdn.ac.uk/about/campus/maps/view/113/</a></p>
        <h3>Accessibility</h3>
        <p>Access to the upper floor of the museum is limited &ndash; contact the museum for details. For a pan-disability access guide to the Zoology building, visit the <a href="https://www.accessable.co.uk/university-of-aberdeen/old-aberdeen-campus/access-guides/zoology-building" target="_blank" alt-text="Accessibility" title="Accessibility">AccessAble</a> website.</p>
        <h2><a href="https://www.abdn.ac.uk/museums/exhibitions/kings-museum-586.php" target="_blank" alt-text="King's Museum" title="King's Museum">King&rsquo;s Museum, Old Aberdeen Town House</a></h2>
        <p>Currently closed for re-development, this small museum will be re-opening in September 2020 with a permanent display about the history of the University of Aberdeen and the Old Aberdeen area.</p>
        <h3>Address:</h3>
        <p>Old Aberdeen Town House, High Street, Aberdeen AB24 3EN</p>
    </div>
</div>